text: Wesley Douglas, born November 28, 1996 in Stoke-on-Trent, is an English rugby player playing for center and winger with CA Brive Corrèze in Top 14 since 2020. Wesley Douglas left England in 2016 to join France and the Pro D2 within the squad of AS Béziers Hérault. In January 2020, he joined CA Brive Corrèze from the 2020-2021 season and discovered the Top 14. == References == Category:English rugby union players Category:1996 births Category:Living people
